    <ownedClass>
        <class isAbstract="false" name="PCRemovalRegistrationEvent">
            <derivationSupplier className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
            <graphicRepresentation presentation="HL7">
                <graphElement containerDiagramName="Main"
                    isHeightAutoSize="true" isWidthAutoSize="false"
                    shapeId="Sheet.253" shapeTemplate="Act">
                    <position x="5.00778" y="8.7"/>
                    <size height="1.04778" width="3.5"/>
                </graphElement>
            </graphicRepresentation>
            <annotations>
                <otherAnnotation type="html">
                    <text>
                        <b>Information (from NHAIS) about a patient being removed (or intending to be removed) from a Primary Care Providers system.</b>
                        <br/>
                    </text>
                </otherAnnotation>
            </annotations>
            <attribute conformance="R" fixedValue="REG"
                isMandatory="true" isStructural="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="classCode" sortKey="1">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>Indicates this is a registration.<br/>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="classCode"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="REG"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" fixedValue="EVN"
                isMandatory="true" isStructural="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="moodCode" sortKey="2">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>Indicates this is an event.<br/>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="moodCode"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="EVN"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" defaultValue="04" fixedValue="04"
                isMandatory="true" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="1" name="code" sortKey="4">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>Indicates the type ofregistration. In this case, it is the removal of a registration of a record onto an NHAIS system. The Coded with Code System datatype flavour is used to carry this information as follows:                                <ul>
                                <li>The <i>code </i>attribute will contain the fixed value shown. </li>
                                <li>The <i>codeSystem </i>attribute will contain the OID "2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.17.165" </li>
                            </ul>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="code" className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CV"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="DemographicRegistrationType"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute isMandatory="false" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="0" name="effectiveTime" sortKey="10">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>The business effective date when this information was applicable.<br/>
                            </p>
                            <p>If both a start date and an end date are present the Date or Time Interval Complete data type shall be used: </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The <i>low</i> attribute shall contain the start date. </li>
                                <li>The <i>high</i> attribute shall contain the end date. </li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>If only a start date is present the Date or Time Interval After data type shall be used: </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The <i>low</i> attribute shall contain the start date. </li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>If only an end date is present the Date or Time Interval Before data type shall be used:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The <i>high</i> attribute shall contain the end date. </li>
                            </ul>All dates will use the Date Only flavour in format YYYYMMDD.</text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="effectiveTime"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="IVL">
                    <supplierBindingArgumentDatatype name="TS"/>
                </type>
            </attribute>
            <attribute isMandatory="false" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="0" name="availabilityTime" sortKey="12">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>The data on which the removal was requested by the remover.</p>
                            <p>Using Date Only flavour - YYYYMMDD. </p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="availabilityTime"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="TS"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="reasonCode" sortKey="20">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>The reason for removal. The Coded with Code System datatype flavour is used to carry this information as follows: <br/>
                            <ul>
                                <li> The <i>code</i> attribute will contain a value from the list of codes in the NHAISRemovalReasonCode vocabulary </li>
                                <li> The <i>codeSystem</i> attribute will contain the OID "2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.17.168" </li>
                            </ul> NOTE: If the source of a retrieval request is not NHAIS, and a current Reason for Removal is set, the PDS will transform the Removal type to "X" ie exited.<br/> If the source of a retrieval request is not NHAIS, and future dated Reasons for Removal are present, the PDS will return these. If the Requesting Authority Organisation Id for the future dated Reason for Removal is not the same as the Organisation Id of the source of the Request (as supplied in the request), the PDS will transform the Removal type to "X" ie exited.<br/> If the source of the retrieval request is NHAIS, and the Reason for Removal, Removal Type is "SDN" or "AFN", then the PDS will transform this to "ORR", i.e. Other Reason.</text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="reasonCode"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CV"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="NHAISRemovalReasonCode"/>
            </attribute>
        </class>
    </ownedClass>
